  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Forehead sensor can predict the more accurate fluid responsiveness than finger sensor in
      children
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The investigator hypothesized that the forehead sensor can predict the fluid responsiveness
      more accurate than the finger sensor in pediatric patients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
